2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
170 g Rigatoni
113 g Mushrooms
56 g Yellow Onion, chopped
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
¼ cup Sun-Dried Tomato Pesto
1 tbsp Cream Sauce Spice Blend
1 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
½ tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
0.13 tsp Salt*
1 tbsp Butter*

Add rigatoni to the boiling water. Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 10-12 min.
Reserve 1 cup (2 cups) pasta water, then drain and return rigatoni to the same pot, off heat.

Meanwhile, slice mushrooms.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When the pan is hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then Beyond Meat® patties. Cook, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**
Transfer Beyond Meat® to a plate. Reserve fat in pan.

Reheat the same pan over medium.
Add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, then onions and mushrooms. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until softened, 5-6 min.
Sprinkle Cream Sauce Spice Blend over top. Stir to coat.

Add pesto, broth concentrate and 1 cup (2 cups) water to the pan, then stir to combine.
Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to medium. Return Beyond Meat® to the pan.
Cover and cook until sauce thickens slightly, 2-4 min.

Add Beyond Meat® and sauce to the pot of rigatoni. Stir to combine. (TIP: For a looser consistency, add reserved pasta water 1-2 tbsp at a time.)
Divide pasta and Beyond Meat® as well as any remaining sauce between bowls.
Sprinkle cheese over top.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, disregard instructions to prep chicken.

Cook Beyond Meat® in the same way as the chicken, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min. ** Disregard instructions to reserve fat in the pan.